parameters: \n<\N[3]>It seems like this elevator is not powered on...

\n<\N[3]>If we can just get it powered on, it should
move... Shall we try to find the distribution
panel?

\n<Announcement>\C[24]Please select the floor level you wish to
use.

\n<\N[3]>Huh...? This elevator can only go between the
\c[2]1st and 3rd floors\c[0]?

\n<\N[3]>Well, the goal is to go to the 3rd floor. Is there
any problem in particular?

\n<Announcement>\C[24]Please select the floor level you wish to
use.

\n<\N[3]>The lights are on... The elevator should be
working now.

\n<\N[3]>The fuse in the distribution panel is broken... So
what those kids were talking about earlier was
this.

\n<\N[3]>Is there a \C[2]fuse\C[0] somewhere...? Or... if
it's the \c[2]distribution room\c[0], it must be
there for sure...

\n<\N[3]>It's functioning properly now that I've inserted
the fuse.
It seems like this elevator is completely stopped.
